column2: Water has been extremely clear all summer. The springs have been flowing well- evidenced by the amount of water going over the spillway- even during the driest weeks. Lots of beaver activity here as usual. Nearby lodges are being maintained and increased in size.
Many large (up to 12 inches x 6 inches) freshwater sponges have been seen. Photos available.

column1: A little pine pollen on the surface of the water.

column2: some pine pollen - not too bad
